Executive Profile
Reuben E. Slone  Senior Vice President of Supply Chain, Retail & Pharmacy Renewal, Walgreens Boots Alliance, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 1 Board Members in 1 different organizations across 4 different industries.See Board Relationships54--
Background

		Mr. Reuben E. Slone has been Senior Vice President of Supply Chain, Retail & Pharmacy Renewal at Walgreens Boots Alliance, Inc. (also known as Walgreen Co.) since May 16, 2012. Mr. Slone served as Senior Vice President of Supply Chain Management at Walgreen Co. since May 16, 2012. Mr. Slone served as an Executive Vice President Supply Chain and General Manager of Services at OfficeMax Incorporated since 2004 until April 16, 2012. He served as Vice President of Global ... e-Business at OfficeMax since April 4, 2000. He joined Whirlpool Corporation from General Motors Corporation in Detroit, where he served as Director, e-sales, in the e-GM Business Unit. Prior to this assignment, Mr. Slone served as Director, Global Manufacturing Strategic Process and System Alignment, in the Information Systems and Services function. Before joining General Motors, Mr. Slone led global strategy, distribution and information technology for Federal-Mogul. Prior to joining Federal-Mogul, Mr. Slone spent almost ten years in management consulting with Ernst & Young and EDS/AT Kearny. In the past, Mr. Slone has held positions of responsibility in the Process Development and Change Management function and also has practiced as a management consultant and practice leader at Electronic Data Systems (EDS) in Troy, Mich. He has been an Independent Director of Advance Auto Parts Inc. since March 7, 2016. In October 2004, Harvard Business Review published his article entitled Leading a Supply Chain Turnaround. Business Week, Computer World and Internet Week all recognized Mr. Slone's efforts in supply chain, the use of the internet and novel uses of information technology. Mr. Slone received a B.S. in engineering from the University of Michigan in 1984 where he graduated cum laude. In 1985 he received a Graduate Fellowship in Mechanical Engineering.Read Full Background




